About

Project Overview

This web application is designed to help estimate missing precipitation data using various interpolation methods. It provides an interactive interface for analyzing rainfall data and applying different estimation techniques.

Built with React and modern web technologies, this tool allows users to:

  • Upload or manually enter precipitation data
  • Visualize station locations on an interactive map
  • Apply different estimation methods
  • Compare results across methods
  • Download processed data for further analysis

Technical Details

Technologies Used

  • React for UI components
  • Tailwind CSS for styling
  • Leaflet.js for map functionality
  • D3.js/Chart.js for data visualization
  • Turf.js for geospatial calculations

Data Storage

All data is stored locally in your browser using localStorage, ensuring your data remains private and accessible across sessions.

Methods Explained

Basic Methods

  • Arithmetic Mean: Simple average of precipitation values from surrounding stations
  • Normal Ratio: Weighted average based on normal precipitation values at each station

Advanced Methods

  • Inverse Distance Weighting:{' '} Considers the distance between stations for weighted averaging
  • Isohyetal Method: Uses lines of equal rainfall for area-weighted averaging
  • Theissen Polygon: Creates polygons around stations for area-weighted calculations
